Brian S. Posner  President, Point Rider Group LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 14 different industries.See Board Relationships56--
Background

		Mr. Brian S. Posner has been the President of Point Rider Group LLC since 2008. Mr. Posner has over 20 years of business experience in financial services and served as private investor since 2008. From 1997 to 1999, he held various executive and other positions with Warburg Pincus Asset Management/Credit Suisse Asset Management and Fidelity Management and Research Company, where he also served as co-Chief Investment Officer and Director of Research. He served as the ... Managing Director, Chief Executive Officer, Co-Chief Investment Officer and President at ClearBridge Advisors, LLC from 2005 to March 31, 2008. He was Co-Founder and Managing Partner of Hygrove Partners LLC since 2000 and served as its Chief Investment Officer. He served as Head of New US Equity Unit at Legg Mason Inc. since November 1, 2005. He served as a Portfolio Manager and Analyst at Fidelity Investments from 1987 to 1996. Mr. Posner served as Managing Director, Co-Chief Investment Officer, Director of Research, Analyst and Portfolio Manager at Warburg Pincus Private Client Group. He served as the President, Chief Executive Officer and Co-Chief Investment Officer at LMP Capital and Income Fund Inc. and ClearBridge Asset Management Inc. He served as Vice President and Investment Officer at Legg Mason Partners Funds Trust - Legg Mason Partners Mid Cap Fund since 2005. He served as Vice President and Investment Officer of ING Life Insurance Variable Annuity Account B - ING Salomon Brothers Capital (alternate name: Salomon Brothers Capital Fund Inc.). He has been Chairman of the Board at Bioverativ Inc. since January 10, 2017. Mr. Posner has been an Independent Director at Biogen Inc. since July 2008. He has been a Director of Arch Capital Group Ltd. since November 4, 2010 and RiverPark Funds since 2010. He served as Director of Anadys Pharmaceuticals Inc. from August 2011 to November 23, 2011. He served as a Director of BG Medicine, Inc. from February 13, 2012 to April 15, 2015. He served as Director of Sotheby's. He serves as a Member of the Board of Visitors for the Weinberg College of Arts and Sciences at the Northwestern University. Mr. Posner holds BA in History from Northwestern University and an M.B.A. in finance from the University of Chicago Graduate School of Business.Read Full Background




